title: The View from the Beach
author: paige
text: the sand between my toes,  the aquatic ocean smell,  the sun shining brightly upon my face,  i can see a panorama of sand and water alike,  and i know that the beach is where i want to be.       the waves crash onto the shore like mad horses in a stampede,  white foam bubbles over the rim of the clear,  blue water.  just when i think they are gone in the current,   they spring back up above the surface,  and i know that the beach is where i want to be.      a cluster of sailboats float by,  they drift slowly over the cool,  splashing ocean,  letting the waves choose their destination for them,  the sails swaying softly in the light breeze,  and i know that the beach is where i want to be.      a motorboat speeds over the salty waves,  making its own decisions,  taking its own chances,   whether they are dangerous and risky or sage and wise,  and i know that the beach is where i want to be.

title: A World Lit by Industry
author: patrick
text: in the midst,  of a checkerboard of fields,  in the heart of america,  across a backdrop of pines as docile as feathers,  began to change.  of no community,   of these peevish disasters upon us almost unnoticed,  in countless towns in america.  in this stricken world like a dynasty,  from the moment of conception until death,  of these chemicals,   in water,  in sodden water,  in the bodies of fish and other animals,  of such fruitless contamination.  of the vast majority,  of us,  of age.  of the sudden rise,  of industry,  on world war was this child born,  to test,  of disheartened death for human beings.

title: Parade
author: patty
text: we're having a parade on this scorching summer day,   this is because it is the first day in may.   blankets and lawn chairs line the street,   now is the time family and friends meet.   ice cream melting in children's hands,   here comes the enormous marching band!  the noise and chaos make a lot of sound,   candy and sweets are thrown onto the ground.    clowns' faces are all sorts of colors,   the clowns are greeted by children and their mothers.   loud,  speedy go-carts go rolling by,   kids throw up their hands to wave and say ''hi!''  parade floats proceed slowly down the parade path,   some floats make people want to laugh.   now that the parade is through,   it is time for you to leave too!

text: jack and jill go up the hill but they donâ’t come tumbling down,  it happens different you will see- it all started in a town.  jack and jill were poor and ill,  seeking for something to trade,  but after a while of searching for miles,  their hope began to fade.  just then a man who ran a stand,  noticed jack and jill,  he took their weeds and gave them seeds,  then told them to run up that hill.  well jack and jill,  naã¯ve still,  listened to the man,  they hurried quick right out of town and ran and ran and ran.  when jack and jill reached the hill,  they went right to that well,  what they found inside,  was quite a surprise-just a small seed and its shell.  â“how dare that man try to trick us like that?â” jill began to cry,  the well that should have water was completely dry.  jack got so mad,  so very mad; he threw the seeds they found,  just then it started to rain and rain,  falling upon the ground.  jack and jill,  soaking still,  noticed the wee little seed,  it shook a little on the ground then sprouted a large green weed.  but it didnâ’t stop there,  it continued to grow taller than most of the trees,  if you saw this beanstalk you would know itâ’s something you never see.  jack and jill,  desperate still,  thought maybe the man was right,  so they climbed on up the beanstalk fast,  boy was it a sight! when they got to the top,  their dreams came true for it was a land of food,  it was huge of course with tons of meals,  but the kids didnâ’t want to be rude.  jack and jill,  polite still,  knocked on all the doors,  but nobody came out; there was no noise,  except for lots of snores.  jack and jill,  hungry still,  followed the annoying noise,  they found a house,  and opened the door and found lots of girls and boys! they were trapped in ropes the size of…well ropes… that were really big,  and what they saw next was very weird; again it was enormous and big.  a giant slept inside a bed snoring really loud,  but among all the mess,  jack and jill,  saw their friends inside the crowd.  hansel and gretel were all tied up,  shh-ing all around,  they didnâ’t want the giant to wake up- for jack and jill to be found.  jack and jill,  puzzled still,  wondered why they were tied up,  so hansel and gretel in,  in a very small voice,  explained why madness erupt.  far from the town up in the sky,  a magic bird was found,   it was very happy there,  you see,  and it layed golden eggs on the ground.  but soon the people of the town became greedy and looked for the bird,  the people searched everywhere up and down,  but it wasnâ’t seen or heard.  so of the children that climbed on up the winding,  tall,  green stalk,  the giant made them slaves to find the bird-they couldnâ’t ever talk.  but still,  they never found the bird,  and to this very day,  the giant makes them search and search-here is where they stay.  the only way the children will be freed,  is to find that magic bird,  but no person has ever seen it-no person has ever heard.  when hansel and gretel had finished their tale they looked so very sad,  jack and jill,  worried still,  knew the giant was bad.  and even though they were very scared,  jack and jill volunteered,  they would find that magic bird,  and travel the journey feared.  they snuck up to the kitchen to find some food that they would need for the trip,  then they put on their boots for the long walk,  a step they could not skip.  after the siblings said their goodbyes,  they headed out the door,  but when they got outside they remembered they needed something more.  a map of course! ,  is what they need to get around the town,  so they went on looking all around,  for someone in the town.  just as the two were about to give up,  they heard a quiet sigh,  and as they approached the girl in red,  she began to cry.  â“whatâ’s wrong?â” asked gretel in a caring tone,  â“iâ’m just looking for a mapâ”,  then the girl sat up and smiled as if they had walked into her trap.  â“iâ’m all aloneâ”,  replied the girl â“will you come and stay with me?â” â“i have no map but surely iâ’m as friendly as can be!â” â“sorry but we have to goâ”,  said jill,  now afraid,  but little red riding hood seemed completely careless that this isnâ’t where they stayed.  she asked where they were going and jack said â“the birdâ”,  so red had to go with them when she heard that very word.  of course she knew the town and the way they had to go,  so she led them up the nearest mountain that was slightly covered in snow.  but wait- this snow wasnâ’t even snow,  they were diamonds shining bright,  â“donâ’t touch themâ”,  said red riding hood,  â“for this is the mountain of snow white\tâ“.  for a boy who grew up with nothing at all jack picked up just one,  but he quickly froze into a statue of ice and now the damage was done.  for the next whole day of the girlsâ’ frightening trip,  jill cried her heart out with a trembling lip.  but she quickly stopped on the following day when she smelled a delightful smell,  it was a river full of chocolate that was flowing from a well.  â“tricky treat river-donâ’t drink from the flow!â” but jill learned her lesson from the mountain of snow.  finally they came to a golden path except the bricks were…eggs! there were so many that when you walked,  they come up to your legs.  this must be where the bird lived and this was proven true,  the girls saw it just sitting there and it looked so very blue.  jill wen to pick up the bird but behind her she heard a sound,  red had grown sharp teeth and her head had turned around! â“ah-ha! youâ’ve fallen for my trick-iâ’m the golden birdâ’s keeper,  i need to rid of any thieves so i made the egg laying deeper.  soon you were supposed to drown but a problem in my plan,  the bird has stopped laying its egg and that is why i ranâ”.  as jill was sinking through the eggs she knew just what to do,  sheâ’d sing the song her parents sang when she had had the flu: â“though you be sick,  or hurt or ill,  you are still strong,  powerful still.  deep in your heart your powers will glow,  and soon you will see,  the brightness will show. â” red was furious and growing weak for she tried to stop the song,  but it was too late- red had shriveled and she was already gone.  jill rose right out of the eggs,  and the bird began laying from between its legs.  the curse was broken and all lives came back,  including the townspeople and of course- jack.  jack and jill rejoiced and they took the bird to town,  here,  everyone was grateful-not a single frown.  and as they came back to the giantâ’s room,  they saw he was gone and the ropes were too.  the children were free and could roam about-their parents had returned as well,  so jack and jill,  homesick still,  went home for a story to tell.  their family liked the town above so they decided to move right away,  and so jack and jill,  heroic still,  knew that they should stay.

title: In Love
author: quinton
text: so deep in love.  so complicated.  been heartbroken so much.  my heart is faded.  i wrote this poem for all the reasons why.  and that i've been down heartbreak road.  and how much it hurts inside.  just by looking at her face i thought she was the one.  they say love is in the eye of the beholder.  and i beheld that love.  but something came over me and i wanted new love.  searching and creeping in all the wrong places.  when the real love was always by my side.  she was always there for me.  but love was something i could no longer see.  but suddenly i was in a place.  a place where you can't run or hide.  that place that was always there by my side.  love was in me.  love was calling me,  writing me.  love was apart of me.  love was something that i could now see.  love was my heart.  love was her.

title: You
author: rachel
text: you \t\t\t\t\t       by: rachel       the last words you said to me were,  â“             iâ’ll miss you too. â”  but our friendship fell apart.  and i donâ’t wanna think about you.   you say you left me for something more.   now youâ’re back so soon,  like you just went to the store.   you act like itâ’s no big deal.   when you were gone,  you hurt me,  for real.   why?  why did you go?  did i say something?  i need to know.   what else can there be?  i thought our friendship meant something more.   what did you leave me for?  i acted so sad and depressed around you.   but you never seemed to care.   i wish i had the courage to ask you why.   it just isnâ’t fair.   you werenâ’t there when i needed you most.   now when i see you,  itâ’s like seeing a ghost.   iâ’ve told you everything,  except one.   when you ask me what i didnâ’t say.   i will reply,  â“ why should i tell you?â”  but the answer is,  i have feelings too.

title: Tonight
author: robyn
text: tonight i sit and think of you what you might be doing,  who you might be with and where you could be going,  what might you do there and what time you'll be home,  i want ring you as i stare at your scented foam,   tonight i lay here wondering when you may return,  what state you might be in and  what you might burn,  who you could bring home and what you might have done,  i wish that i was with you but you seem to be having fun,   tonight i sleep and dream of you and run through your thoughts,  what could happen to you when your down by the ports,  why did you run away from me on this quiet night,  what was the point of jumping from such a height,   tonight i sit here mourning you wondering why you did it,  in early hours of today i didnt imagne this for a minute,  what was the point i wonder? was it just to hurt me,  you were my life i needed you i thought we got along,  but did we?

title: School
author: robyn
text: it's early mornings and back to school we go tomorrow,  the annoying people who are always asking to borrow,   waiting in the cold for the old school bus,  the drivers dont honestly care about us.   in the morning during first lesson wanting to go back to bed,  the teachers dont understand why we have a sleepy head,  second lesson getting a bit more awake,  but most of us already have a headache.   breack time comes and we have a snack,  the bell goes but we dont wont to go back,  we make our way to the classroom,  for those boring lessons to resume.   third lesson passes by we never really listen,  looking out the windows watching the sun glisten,  nearly lunchtime only one long hour,  at lunch we can eat sweets both normal and sour.   last lesson is coming up one hour and we get to go home,  the bell goes and were all alloud to wonder and roam,  we get on the bus and begin our boring bus ride,  homewrok when we get in  then we can hide.  a good nights sleep is needed for the next morning,  being waken up early without any warning,  now our journey starts all over again,  school really does drive me insain.

title: The Pond
author: sadie
text: the moons reflecting in a tiny pond,  while revealing its true light.  seeing image after image in the middle of the night.  tiny water flies bounce from one spot to another,  leaving ripples everytime they drop.  delicate little fire flies shine bright as the night grows warmer.  flashing it's glowing light oh so very often.  the moon begins to set and the sum begins to rise.  leaving behind all the beauty,  waiting for another day to arrive.

title: Sledding
author: sadie
text: as i hop on my sled,  old and rusty,  i hear the white snow thump on my head.  i gingerly walk to the top of the hill and ask my sister to give me a push.   i start racing straight down the hill,  as fast as a speed boat.  i see the brown bark of the tree trunk coming closer and closer to me.   i try to turn the sled so i won't hit  the tree,  but it was too late. . .  crash!!! i run right into the tree! i take off my snow gear to go inside.   i smell the hot flaming fire when i walk into the living room.  i ask my mom to make me a hot  cup of cocoa.   i hear the whistle of the tea pot and the boiling water splash into the cup.  i take a sip and taste the drink slip down my throat.

title: Love and Hardship
author: sadie
text:
you are here for me,  even though you are not.  you are in a way,  i sit there everyday,  and see you having fun,  but i'm sitting there,  feeling pushed away.   when you are around,  i feel happy but,  i never know what to say.  i stand there looking at you,  and feel like i'm alone even though,  im crowded in the small space,  being pushed around.   i sit in 6 different rooms every day,  and i think about you everyday.  sometimes they are not the best thoughts,  but sometimes (just sometimes) i think some good.   i think of you all the time and feel as if,   i don't belong.   but i stay with you forever no matter how i feel  because no matter how many times,   i feel left out i stay because i still love you.  << /p=\>

title: Footsteps
author: sam
text: did you notice,  how footsteps sound? they can make loud and soft noises,  or they can be wide and hollow.   footsteps can be found inside the house,  or outside in the streets.  they can be found most anywhere,  just think!  if you hear footsteps,   you quickly turn around.  thinking someone's following you,  but have you ever really listened?  instead of turning,  listen to the beat they make.  they can make fast or slow beats,  and it doesn't matter where they are.   have you ever listened to footsteps? have you really tried? did you stop to meet the beat,  or just walk away?  try listening to the footsteps,  maybe you'll see.  how neat little things in the world,  can be.

title: Hidden Beauty

title: My Little Doggie
author: samantha
text: i have a dog whose brown and white; he does not like the bright sun light.  he rolls on the floor and runs after a ball.  for six months old,  he is very small.  he has sad looking eyes,  and when i come home after school he always seems surprised.  my little dog has long hanging ears,  and my dog absolutely fears the cat that lives next door.  my doggie runs into walls and hops through the upstairs halls.  my doggie is kind of dumb,  but he is a bucket full of fun.  my doggie follows me everywhere i can't make him stop,  but i know he does it because he loves me a lot.  my doggie is my special friend; he will be there until the end.

title: The Power of Music
author: samvit

''people expect the spectacle,  they want the theatrical,  and all too soon they forget the real purpose,  the true reason,  a genuine ruler.  his royalness is as royal as a butterfly, his commoness is as common as a caterpillar, his thrown is built with his good deeds, his efforts and services fashion him a royal robe, his justice is his staff,  his honesty embellish it with precious stones, his majesty is his mighty heart and the look upon his people's faces when he rescues and takes care of them,  is his glorious crown.  a king only eats after his people have eaten.  he does not sleep until his people are safe.  he crowns himself with goodness and wears jewels of purity,  humility and wisdom.

title: Guitar Player

title: Cleats
author: scott
text: the cleats are worn and dirty,  frayed laces on each side,  i love the way they grip the grass,  covered with morning dew.   without them the game would be changed,  would not be the same.   cleats get dirty and marked up,  each mark having a meaning,  having a moment,  all a different game.   the time is here,  time to put them away,  in the closet they will stay.  until next season is near.

title: Florida

title: Break of Dawn
author: scott
text: as the sun rises,  a billowing,  golden bloom,  the weeping willows come to life,  no longer in darkness' gloom.   the waters shimmer an eerie light,  calm serene and still.  the light is cast upon it in such a way,  that is seems to move of its own free      will the mountains loom in the distance,  dark and regal and steep.  the snow swept caps are cheerful and bright,  while the sheer cliffs are icy and sleek.   the river winds a steady path,  through the meadows as a snake.  the rapids glance foam off the rocks,  leaving broken driftwood in its wake.   the leaves on the gnarled,  ancient branches,  seem to shine from within.  their vibrant colors gleam with dew,  they rustle with a soft,  soothing din.   the break of dawn brings many suprises,  no matter what our heart or mind surmises,  nature is full of wonderful,  beautiful prizes,  if only we have the time to look.

title: ''Tests''
author: shea
text: i hate tests.  tests hate me.  that's my excuse for getting a d.  i study hard,  and i study long,  but no matter the question,  i'm always wrong.  i try to do good,  maybe even great,  but it's always the same old 68(they say my brain is made of fluff,  or some weird unnatural stuff).  when i get my test in the mail of the week,  i hide it from my parents,  but they always sneak a peek.  afterwards they start fussing and shouting,  and,  on occasion,  even start pouting! they yell, '' oh! dear boy,  can't you do better?'' (if i do manage to hide it,  they always get a letter).  i say to them,  ''i hate tests.  tests hate me.  that's my excuse for getting a d. '' it works really well,  it works without harm.  it works every time,  it works like a charm.

text: i'm glad i'm me.  no one looks the way i do, i have noticed that it's true.  no one walks the way i walk,  no one talks the way i talk.  no one says the things i say,  i'm special! i'm me! and there's no one i'd rather be than me,  sweet me.

title: Rain
author: sissy
text: rain is sad,  but it helps nature grow; we have to put up with the bad to make the best seem better; the soft beat of rain on the roof has a rhythm,  a song,  leaving petals a more gental color than when the sun was shining; rain makes lofe temporarily cold,  wet and lonely,  but when it's gone,  the whole world is bright and cheery,  refreshing every living thing,  perfecting them from the inside out.

title: Insepearable
author: skylar
text: go inside my mind.  deep within, i see the forests, hills,  and valleys of my thoughts.  and the river that fed my endless dreams.   i played there when i was a young one.  i played there every season.  first came spring and summer,  when my mind floated through thunderstorms and distant places.   with the fall,  my head filled with blazing colors of the midday sun.  in winter frosty white patterns lay within.   we have been together a long time,  my imagination and i.  go deep inside my mind

title: Love Sonnet
author: skylar
text: the beautiful white clouds are like your face.  your eyes,  as blue as the sea.  the sky can't surpass your beauty and grace.  i hear the music of angels,  a sweet melody.  the sun comes up and i think of thee.  the warmth on my face,  its like stars in the breeze.  your elegant hair is lke lace.  love is all i want from you.   the rain of midday is like tears.  the sunset makes me think of you.  i was just kidding,  none of its true.

title: My Hero
author: smilez
text: my hero is not cartoon a puppet or a doll,  my hero is not a made up man,  my hero does not have super powers,  my hero saves me when i'm scared and tells me it's ok,  my hero is my dad and i'm so lucky i see him every day.

title: Birds
author: smit
text: as beautiful as a rainbow respectful,  nurturing,  and affable never pensive never mortify anyone always boisterous unique in their own way some are lazy some are hardworkers enjoy flight always happy always living as a family sometimes fighting but still they are birds.

title: Showers of steel
author: smith
text: a tear rolls down my cheek showers of steel fall on my heart,  i feel broken,  i feel weak but it ain't the ending,  it's just the start.   as i think about it a shiver goes down my spine,  i don't wanna lose my friends i don't wanna lose something,  which has become so mine.   is this fair? i don't think so when them buddies have grown so near to me,  parents tell me to let go.   i was never told that don't let your friends near as i remember those happy moments,  i shed a tear.   how i spend my childhood in the lanes,  but then suddenly,  daddy tells me leave'em now.  mommy's health's falling we gotta go back,  wow!  i'll have to abandon the staircase that took me up,  that took me down,  i'll have to forget the four walls that saw me smile,  that saw me frown!  i must not think about the swing again where i had countless hours of fun,  but oh my mind! how it craves oh my mind! how it hunts.   how it hunts for the time i spent in here,  when i see our old pictures my bones start crunching,  no more i can bear.   i wish i could rewind the moments,  and relive,  but i ain't got no strength,  while i can't take it anymore and am about to blast,  but i can't shed a tear,  'cuz boys don't cry,  my friend!

title: My Mind Is Like
author: someone
text: my mind is like a soccer ball,  big and round but full of air.  when i am thinking i just sit and stare.  my mind can learn things very quick but soon burn out like a wick.   things i learn come and go,  like a boomerang thrown out a window.  my attention span is not very long,  it has as much patience as king kong.  if there is something i do not understand,  don't try to explain; i'll be in my own little land.

title: Dear mummy & papa
author: sona
text: your little kid has to say something. .  you know!  i never wanted to hide anything you both are my life,  even if i became someone's wife.  please forgive my attitude,  by which i had loosen your grattitude. .  sorry !  for i gave you pain,  sorry ! for that i did. .  you are my strength,  through your blessings i can measure any length.  my tears are only for you,  my life is because of you. .  please,  don't ever think,  to keep me away from you,  because my life is because of you  and only for you without you. .  nothing is mine and nothing is i. .

title: Dancers Are People Who...
author: sonja
text: dancers are people who are dedicated.  dancers are always tense,  always alert.   dancers would do anything for their art,  anything to land a perfect spinning jump.   dancers are delicate,  dancers know,  live,  and breathe their moves.   every move they make is like a dance,  and life is just a song that seems to have no end.   dancers are very graceful,  dancers are glistening with pride.   dancers are admired each time they take a stride,  dancers stand up tall with their heads held high.   for they are proud of what they do,  dancers are people who are heroes.

title: The One Bright Light

text: the light comes over the edge of life blinding anyone in its path it reaches me  i can no longer see what once was bold is now gold my life is finally complete

title: Natures Beautiful Birds
author: sophia
text: i love birds who mesmerize all creatures with their beauty who are light as a feather who fly around at their leisure who eat from my bird feeders who are animated and spirited who are docile yet haughty birds that are boisterous birds that are peevish birds that scurry around on the ground birds that alight in maple trees     birds that bring out natures true beauty
